description:
We went there last Wed, booked for 8:30pm, 9 people + 1 baby:
- first of all when reserving for big parties they ask you for credit card and charge $25 if you do not show up;
- when we arrived, we were unable to sit down before 9pm despite we arrived in time, for people with babies you know what that mean loosing 30 minutes waiting. When they were explaining why the delay, it seemed the most normal thing to wait 30 minutes beyond reservation;
- we had to have fixed menu in "family style" as they are not even able to process 9 different orders per table;
- they served us 7 very small appetizers for 9 people, $42 per person, drinks and desserts NOT included, that was it! Even the meat balls were counted, 1 per person, unbelievable.

I think I ate more bread than actual food, that was the only way to stop the hunger, as food was sufficient probably for 5 or 6 people, not 9.
If you want to have good Spanish cuisine there are better places for less money.
